<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin: Balance Between Powers `Taking Shape' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin: Balance Between Powers `Taking Shape' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004145394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1402 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Apr -- "A balance between the executive 
and representative powers is taking shape." This was stated by 
Russian Federation President Boris Yeltsin at a meeting with the 
heads of administrations of Russian krays and oblasts, when he 
was summing up the results of elections to local bodies of power 
that had been held in a number of regions. 
  According to Boris Yeltsin, "the elections were normal, 
though not everywhere was their quality good." In June there 
will be elections in the rest of the regions. "We must continue 
work to truly provide a real division of power," stressed Boris 
Yeltsin. 

</TEXT>

