<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Urges Regional Leaders Sign Civic Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Urges Regional Leaders Sign Civic Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004141994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1206 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 20 TASS -- "The political situation in 
Russia began to stabilise", Russian President Boris Yeltsin told 
a meeting with regional leaders on Wednesday. He confirmed that 
the civic accord agreement is to be signed in the Kremlin on 
April 28 and said that nearly 140 political and piblic 
organisations are going to join it. 
  Yeltsin urged all branches of authority, political parties 
and public organisations to sign the agreement and called on all 
Russian regional leaders to follow suit. The president proposed 
to regional leaders to "meet regularly, in small groups" in 
order to "frankly speak and discuss all regional problems". 

</TEXT>

