passed a vote of confidence in the government. The confidence 
motion, for which 51 deputies voted in favor, was proposed by 
the Latvian Way group. 
  After the vote, Prime Minister Valdis Birkavs said: 
  [Begin Birkavs recording] I am satisfied, not because I have 
kept my post, but because the government will have the 
opportunity to further implement the declaration intended by the 
government. [end recording] 

