<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko on Promoting CIS Cooperation, Harmony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shumeyko on Promoting CIS Cooperation, Harmony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904184694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1200 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] [Announcer L. Panova] Vladimir Shumeyko, chairman of 
the Federal Assembly [as heard], held a routine traditional 
roundtable in Moscow today. The journalists who assembled there 
learned about his views on a number of currently topical issues, 
specifically, on developing cooperation between CIS countries. 
  [Begin Shumeyko recording] As chairman of the Council of 
Heads of State, the president has proposed drawing up a 
long-term plan. Two councils of ministers -- the Council of 
Foreign Ministers and the Council of Defense Ministers -- have 
been instructed to prepare an initial document, a draft plan for 
CIS development toward integration. [end recording] 
  [Panova] In Vladimir Shumeyko's view, after such a plan is 
adopted, the CIS charter will be somewhat amended. 
  [Begin Shumeyko recording] The point is that it was very 
clearly mentioned at the Council of Heads of State and at the 
Council of Heads of Government that members of the Commonwealth 
must not be in a state of war with each other. There is, 
perhaps, no other case in the whole world when members of the 
same commonwealth are fighting each other. I am speaking about 
Azerbaijan and Armenia. [end recording] 
  [Panova] Regarding Russia joining the NATO Partnership for 
Peace program, Shumeyko stressed that a clear mechanism for 
implementing decisions is the main condition to be observed here. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

