<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Incident With Order on CIS Military Bases `Closed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Incident With Order on CIS Military Bases `Closed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904145794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1340 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and </F>
Aleksandr Krylovich] 
  [Text] Moscow, 19 Apr -- The Russian Foreign Ministry 
believes that the incident which arose in connection with a 
publication of "an order by the Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
on setting up military bases in CIS states and Latvia" is 
closed. This was announced today at a briefing by Mikhail 
Demurin, deputy director of the Foreign Ministry's Information 
and Press Department. 
  He underlined that "all the necessary explanations have been 
provided at the necessary level. We will not provide any 
further explanations". 
  M. Demurin reiterated that "no one has seen this document" 
at 
the Russian Foreign Ministry. Therefore, he said, "it would be 
very strange to carry out some or other investigation at the 
Foreign Ministry with regard to a document prepared by the 
president's administration, if that is indeed the case." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-17144 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov077_d_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-077 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Orders Power-Sharing Talks With Chechnya </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Orders Power-Sharing Talks With Chechnya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2104095394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 20 Apr 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2104095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Untitled Directive No. 189-rp of the Russian Federation </F>
President, dated 15 April 1994 and signed by Russian Federation 
President B. Yeltsin] 
  [Text] Based on the need for the political regulation of 
relations between federal organs of state power and Republic of 
Chechnya organs of state power: 
  1. The Russian Federation Government is to hold 
consultations with representatives of organs of state power and 
all Chechen Republic political movements with the aim of getting 
out of the sociopolitical situation that has developed, and on 
their basis is to prepare a draft treaty on delimiting areas of 
control between federal organs of state power and Chechen 
Republic organs of state power and on the reciprocal delegation 
of powers. 
  2. The Russian Federation President's Administration and 
leaders of federal organs of state power are to give the 
necessary assistance in holding the consultations referred to in 
paragraph 1 of this directive. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] 15 April 1994 

</TEXT>

