<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bases To Be Established in CIS States With Consent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bases To Be Established in CIS States With Consent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004182594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1655 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Andrey Palaria and Sergey </F>
Ostanin] 
  [Text] Moscow April 20 TASS--Russia will set up military 
bases in CIS states with their consent, Russian Defence Minister 
Pavel Grachev said on Wednesday. 
  The announcement was made after the signing of an 
inter-governmental agreement on military and technical 
cooperation between Russia and Turkey in Moscow today. 
  Grachev said Russia will have three military bases in 
Georgia 
and two in Armenia. In Azerbaijan, Russia plans to establish a 
military facility which is vital not only for Russia, but also 
for other CIS states. He said it will be a missile warning post 
in Gaballa. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

