<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev To Brief NATO Officials on Partnership Stance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev To Brief NATO Officials on Partnership Stance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004170794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1556 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Andrey Palaria and Sergey </F>
Ostanin] 
  [Text] Moscow April 20 TASS--Russian Defence Minister Pavel 
Grachev will visit Brussels on May 25-26 to inform NATO 
officials about Russia's position on the Partnership for Peace 
programme. 
  Following recent NATO air strikes in Bosnia, the Russian 
Defence Ministry "has slightly reviewed its stand on the matter, 
taking into account the position Russia holds in Europe and in 
the rest of the world," Grachev said. 
  Speaking at a meeting with visiting Turkish Defence Minister 
Mehmet Golhan in Moscow on Wednesday, Grachev said that during 
his visit to Brussels he will also brief the defence ministers 
of NATO and other countries on the key provisions of Russia's 
military doctrine. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

