<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Charges Serb Actions Unjustified </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Charges Serb Actions Unjustified </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004201294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1916 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Apr -- The bombardment by Bosnian Serbs 
of civilian targets in Gorazde cannot be justified and goes 
against the interests of the Serbs themselves and against the 
interests of Russia, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev 
said today, speaking before journalists after talks with 
international mediators Lord Owen and Thorvald Stoltenberg. 
  At the same time, Russia's chief diplomat continued, it is 
impossible to agree with the logic of increasing NATO air 
strikes in so far as this would run the risk of an escalation. 
It would be a mistake on the part of NATO and the Western 
states to make a decision on the possibility of further military 
escalation without at least simultaneously having a coordinated 
political approach. 
  Now, more than ever before, Kozyrev emphasized, the time has 
come for Russia, the United States, the United Nations, and the 
European Union to work out a joint political stance before the 
conflicting sides, so that they are left with no doubts 
reagarding the need to come to an agreement instead of going 
from one crisis to another. At the same time, the Serbian side 
must understand that each step along the path of a comprehensive 
cessation of hostilities will be accompanied by a corresponding 
lifting of sanctions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

