<H3> <TI>   Duma To Consider Lifting Yugoslav Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma To Consider Lifting Yugoslav Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204084194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0825 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 22 TASS -- The Russian State Duma 
decided on Friday to hold parliamentary hearings on lifting 
sanctions against Yugoslavia. 
  The proposal was made by Aleksandr Vengerovskiy, deputy 
chairman of the Liberal Democratic Party of Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy. 
  He also proposed to invite to the hearings representatives 
of 
all conflicting sides in former Yugoslavia. 
  Vengerovskiy said that, according to his information, 
representatives of Yugoslavia, Bosnian Serbs, Krajina Serbs, and 
Croatia "had already expressed the wish to participate in such 
hearings". 

</TEXT>

