<F P=102>   LD2104124194 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1045 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tskhinvali, 21 Apr -- Russian troops deployed at the 
Russian-Georgian border, stepped up controls at the Roki tunnel 
near Buron village. Representatives of narcotics businesses, 
who used to smuggle vast amounts of narcotics, opposed this 
step. Making the controls tougher also caused discontent among 
the Ossetian separatists. 
  An IBERIA correspondent was told at the headquarters of the 
Georgian peacekeeping troops deployed in Tskhinvali that the 
Ossetian population of Tskhinvali had held a rally where they 
demanded that the Russian border troops be moved from the 
northern border of the so-called South Ossetia because the 
presence of the troops there means demarcating the state border 
between Russia and Georgia. 

</TEXT>

