<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian, Adygey Accepted as Adygeya State Languages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian, Adygey Accepted as Adygeya State Languages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104174094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0944 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Zhilyakov] </F>
  [Text] Maykop (Republic of Adygeya), 21 Apr -- From today 
there will be two state languages in the Republic of Adygeya -- 
Russian and Adygey. A law to this effect has been adopted by 
the republican parliament. While upgrading Adygey to the level 
of a state language and giving it state support, the legislative 
assembly at the same time did not downgrade Russian or discredit 
it. It did not discriminate against the Russian-speaking 
residents of the republic in any way. "Knowledge or lack of 
knowledge of a language does not provide sufficient grounds for 
any restriction of the rights of the citizens of the Republic of 
Adygeya", stipulates one of the opening articles of the law. 

</TEXT>

