<H3> <TI>   Minsk Hopes To Pay Off Gas Debts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minsk Hopes To Pay Off Gas Debts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2104192094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1715 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2104192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The suspension of central heating in our homes has 
not yet accelerated the clearance of our debt to Russia's 
Gazprom. As we were told by the Belarusian State Company for 
Gas Transportation and Delivery Beltranshaz, over the first 
three and a half months of this year, we amassed 165 billion 
rubles [R] in debt, while our total [word indistinct] now stands 
at R331 billion. We will likely be able to service our debts 
with gas suppliers only after unification with the Russian 
monetary system. For a while, our republic receives energy 
resources in full volume, though, in line with the agreement, we 
should clear our debts by 1 June because, beginning 1 July, gas 
will be delivered to us only according to advance payments. 

</TEXT>

