<H3> <TI>   Buffer Zones Created on Polish, Lithuanian Borders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buffer Zones Created on Polish, Lithuanian Borders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2104135894 Minsk ZVYAZDA in Belarusian 20 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> WS2104135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk ZVYAZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Changes at the Border"] </F>
  [Text] Following Brest Oblast, a border zone has also been 
established on the Belarusian-Polish border in Grodno Oblast. 
The oblast executive committee has approved a list of village, 
settlement, and hamlet soviets, which crisscross the border 
zone. The Border Troops have vacated plots of land located 
within 800 meters of the state border to their engineering 
facilities, including land on which barriers and other 
facilities were previously located. 
  The oblast executive committee has also established a border 
zone ranging from between 200 and 500 meters along the 
Lithuanian border, including plots of land on which checkpoints 
have been erected. These regulations have been introduced 
according to the Belarusian Cabinet of Ministers resolution "On 
Measures for Implementing the Belarusian Republic Legislation on 
the State Border of the Republic of Belarus." Rayon executive 
committees and commanders of military units have been requested 
to explain these measures to the general population. 

</TEXT>

