<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Radetskyy: Talks `Constructive' </H4>

<F P=102> WS2104143294 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2104143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian-Russian negotiations are under way, aimed 
at coordinating the implementation of the Black Sea Fleet 
agreement signed by Boris Yeltsin and Leonid Kravchuk on 15 
April in Moscow. Negotiations to this effect began in Sevastopol 
today, attended by the Ukrainian and Russian defense ministers. 
After the face-to-face talks between Defense Ministers Vitaliy 
Radetskyy and Pavel Grachev, the Ukrainian and Russian 
delegations began an expanded dialogue with the fleet's staff. 
After the personal meeting with his Russian colleague, Vitaliy 
Radetskyy told journalists that the dialogue was continuing in a 
constructive atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

