<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fleet Brigade Officers Protest Ukrainian Takeover </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fleet Brigade Officers Protest Ukrainian Takeover </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104165794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1100 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" program] </F>
  [Text] The 116th Izmail Riverine Brigade of the Black Sea 
Fleet is one of the formations, which, in keeping with the 
decree of Vitaliy Radestskyy, Ukrainian minister of defense, is 
to be reshaped and replaced under the command of that country's 
Navy. 
  Reacting to that step, the Ukrainian military commanders, 
the 
officers in the brigade, resolutely disagree with any unilateral 
actions aimed at changing the status of the formation. In a 
statement adopted at a general meeting, the officers and warrant 
officers demanded that a political decision should be adopted as 
soon as possible on the future of the Black Sea Fleet, on the 
basis of which the fate of each of them could be determined. At 
the same time they warned that, until such a decision is 
adopted, they will stop any attempts to unlawfully seize the 
ships or other facilities belonging to the brigade. 

</TEXT>

