<H3> <TI>   State Duma Delegation Arrives in Belgrade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Delegation Arrives in Belgrade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104203494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2009 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Kondrashov] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, 21 Apr--A parliamentary delegation from 
the Russian State Duma arrived today in Belgrade. Its aim is to 
study the present situation in the republics of the former 
Yugoslavia and inform all the deputies about the results of the 
study with the subsequent aim of discussing the issue in the 
parliament. The delegation, which includes representatives of 
most of the factions, is led by Nikolay Bezborodov, deputy 
chairman of the State Duma Committee for Defense and Security. 

