<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin, Germany's Rexrodt Discuss Economic Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin, Germany's Rexrodt Discuss Economic Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104144994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1413 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Kalintsev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, April 21 (TASS) -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin met with visiting German Minister of 
Economics Guenter Rexrodt on Thursday to discuss prospects for 
economic cooperation between Russia and Germany. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS, Rexrodt said they discussed 
joint projects, all in all 15, ways to boost bilateral trade and 
increase german investments in Russia. Special attention was 
paid to the creation of a favourable climate for German 
investors. However, this will require the Russian parliament to 
adopt certain laws, he added. 
  The German minister believes that economic issues will 
feature prominently during Russian President Boris Yeltsin's 
upcoming visit to Germany scheduled for May. Some of the 
projects that were discussed today will be considered by Yeltsin 
and German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in Bonn. It is unclear as yet 
whether or not cooperation agreements will be signed during his 
visit. It is much more important that the talks in Germany 
should give a new impetus to bilateral economic relations. 
  Germany welcomes Russia's willingness to conclude an 
agreement on partnership and cooperation with the European 
Union. However, this will take some time as it is necessary to 
take into account the interests of eu countries and meet some 
conditions, including adopt certain laws in Russia, the minister 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

