  When ITAR-TASS asked whether recent frequent visits to 
Moscow 
by representativies of Latin American countires are coincidental 
or testify to the activization of Russia's Latin American 
foreign policy, Demurin noted that the Russian Foreign Ministry 
strives to be equally active and dynamical in all directions. 
"Being a great power, we cannot put on the brakes or step on the 
gas or dash off to one or the other region," he emphasised. 

