<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moldova Pledges To Pay Gas Debts by May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moldova Pledges To Pay Gas Debts by May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104192094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1626 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] 21 April TASS -- Moldovan Prime 
Minister Andrei Sangheli said the Republic would settle its 
debts for the gas supplied by Russia's Gasprom gas company by 
the end of May. 
  Last week, the Russian state-run gas giant cut down 
deliveries to Moldova by one third and threatened to cut off gas 
supplies completely unless the Republic repaid its debt. 
  According to Sangheli, Moldova has already paid off part of 
its gas debt. The point at issue now is 108 billion rubles owed 
by Moldovan gas consumers, mostly from the Dniester region which 
is suffering grave economic difficulties at the moment. The 
Moldovan prime minister reported that Kishinev and Tiraspol 
experts were presently considering possibilities of finding 
money to urgently repay the republic's debt. He expressed hope 
that the issue would be solved by joint efforts and supplies of 
Russian gas would be resumed in the full volume. 

</TEXT>

