<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet: Managers Responsible for Gas Payments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet: Managers Responsible for Gas Payments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2104161794 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2104161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We received a report today from the press service 
of the Ukrainian president and the Ukrainian Cabinet of 
Ministers. 
  Who will pay for gas? The government is referring to 
nonpayments for Russian gas used by Ukrainian enterprises. An 
agreement on settling Ukraine's gas debts in the sum of $500 
million was reached with the leadership of the Russian joint 
stock company Gasprom. [Words indistinct] over the first three 
months of the current year, our enterprises paid only 20-25 
percent of the required amount. Considering this situation, 
acting Prime Minister Yukhym Zvyahilskyy today held an extended 
meeting with leaders of certain ministries and departments, 
representatives of oblast administrations, and managers of 
production associations which amass enormous gas debts. 
Opportunities for the branches and enterprises, in particular 
the Ministry of Industry and the Ministry of [word indistinct] 
to clear their debts at the expense of their production were 
discussed. Specific measures aimed at making payments next 
month -- which must be carried out under the personal 
responsibility of enterprise managers -- were also detailed at 
this meeting. The oblast state administration was authorized to 
pressure debtor enterprises. If they fail to make these 
payments, managers of enterprises and local administrations will 
bear all responsibility for the economic and social 
(?consequences), which may follow after gas deliveries to 
enterprises, which have not cleared their gas debts, are 
suspended. 

</TEXT>

