<H3> <TI>   `Centrist Faction' in Parliament Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Centrist Faction' in Parliament Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2104154894 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2104154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We are going to build socialism following the 
European model with the equality of rights for various forms of 
ownership -- this according to entrepreneur Yayhen Shcherbanin, 
a winner in the recent Supreme Council elections, at the news 
conference in Donetsk. 
  At the same time, the establishment of a centrist faction in 
the republican legislature was announced. This faction was 
established by the Donbass-based fund for the promotion of 
progressive reforms, which includes managers of large industrial 
factories and companies. All of them represent the authorities. 
[Words indistinct] will become deputies of the new Supreme 
Council who share goals and tasks of the fund's program. It is 
also taken into consideration that deputies from other oblasts 
of Ukraine will join this faction. According to members of this 
faction, the holding of early presidential elections is 
inadvisable. They believe that Leonid Kravchuk's powers should 
be prolonged until a new Ukrainian constitution is adopted. The 
immediate goal of the faction is to foster the establishment [as 
heard] of Soviets on all levels. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

