<H3> <TI>   U.S. To Provide Aid in Aral Sea Disaster Clear-Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. To Provide Aid in Aral Sea Disaster Clear-Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104161094 Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN in Russian 1023 GMT 21 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] -- On 20 April in 
Tashkent, the Government of Uzbekistan signed a memorandum with 
the U.S. Agency for International Development on the provision 
of help to the population of the Aral region. Khorezm Oblast 
and the Republic of Karakalpakstan will receive technical 
assistance, materials, and equipment to improve the quality of 
drinking water and the sanitary-hygienic and ecological 
education of the population. This scheme is part of the overall 
package of help measuring $15 million for the Republics of 
Central Asia, which was announced by U.S. Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher last autumn. The implementation of the 
scheme will allow an improvement in sanitary and hygienic 
conditions for 500,000 people in the Aral region. 

</TEXT>

