<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani Shelling of Armenian Borders Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azerbaijani Shelling of Armenian Borders Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104204894 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1950 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2104204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1950 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Armenian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani Army shelled Armenia's borders on 
the evening of 20 April and tonight. The Armenian Defense 
Ministry press service reports that the defensive positions 
around Berkavan and [place name indistinct] in Noyemberyanskiy 
Rayon, and Chinari and Movses villages in Tavushskiy Rayon came 
under shelling until midnight from various types of weapons. 
Our border guards were forced to retaliate. 
  Disregarding the agreement on a cease-fire, the armed 
formations in Nakhichevan shelled the border positions near 
Brnakot and Shaghat in Sisianskiy Rayon with an armored vehicle, 
grenade launchers, and howitzers between 2000 and 2100 on the 
same day. The Armenian border guards did not retaliate. These 
same villages were again shelled from Nakhichevan at noon on 21 
April. The enemy used grenade launchers. There are no 
casualties. We have not received any more information on the 
border situation today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

