<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Kerosene Distribution Completed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Kerosene Distribution Completed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104152094 Yerevan SNARK in English 1740 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 20 April (SNARK) -- The American 
Government's humanitarian action on the gratuitous distribution 
of kerosene to the residents in need is over in Armenia. 
  Harry Gilmore, American ambassador to Armenia told SNARK 200 
thousand families of the three largest cities of Armenia have 
got the kerosene. 
  Mr. Gilmore outlined the difficulties they met while the 
shipment of kerosene through the Georgian territory. He said 
Georgian authorities don't control the situation in the regions. 
  "American Government would prefer to deliver the kerosene 
through Turkey," said the ambassador. But the Turkish 
authorities declared they would give their consent on the 
shipment, provided [there was] the progress in the settlement of 
the Karabakh conflict. 
  He confirmed that some families didn't get the kerosene. But 
he assured that according to the mutual agreement of American 
and Armenian sides they will get it during the next stage of the 
distribution in Autumn. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

