<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhazia Government To Sit in Zugdidi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhazia Government To Sit in Zugdidi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104153394 Yerevan SNARK in English 1110 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 20 April (SNARK) -- According to an order 
of the Georgia's Cabinet of Ministries, now the Government of 
Abkhazia will sit in Zugdidi city, instead of Tbilisi. 
  The order, which was published in "SVOBODNAYA GRUZIA" 
newspaper, allows the Georgian Corporation of TV and Radio 
Broadcast to censor information about Abkhazian-Georgian 
relations. 
  The Defence Ministry of Georgia has been charged to present 
a 
concrete plan of special actions at the zone of Kodor canyon in 
Western Georgia to the Coordinating Headquarters on Abkhazian 
problems till 20 April. 

</TEXT>

