<H3> <TI>   Armenian Attacks in Northern Karabakh Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Attacks in Northern Karabakh Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104171894 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2104171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Defense Ministry press service report for 21 April" -- </F>
read by announcer] 
  [Text] Armenia's Armed Forces tried to launch a new attack 
in northern Karabakh on the afternoon of 20 April. Having 
massed a considerable number of troops and hardware in this 
sector, the enemy launched an attack against the settlements in 
northern Agdamskiy Rayon. Heavy fighting continued this morning 
around Guludzha and (?Suma). 
  The situation also remains tense in the southwest part of 
our 
Republic. Heavy fighting continued near Fizuli yesterday, last 
night, and early this morning. Our troops inflicted heavy 
counterblows on the enemy and forced it to withdraw from a 
number of heights. The fleeing enemy left behind a considerable 
amount of arms and military hardware. Our soldiers seized one 
Armenian tank, one infantry fighting vehicle, two Grad 
launchers, 11 cannons, five machine guns, seven radio sets, one 
vehicle, numerous grenade launchers, and automatic weapons. 

</TEXT>

