<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fierce Fighting Rages in Nagorno-Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fierce Fighting Rages in Nagorno-Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104122094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1102 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 21 Apr -- Fighting in Nagorno-Karabakh has 
intensified markedly. The press service of the Nagorno-Karabakh 
Defense Army told ITAR-TASS by telephone that Azerbaijani forces 
mounted a big, two-pronged offensive today. In the Fizuli 
sector, attacks by Azerbaijani tanks are being supported by 
combat planes. One Azerbaijani tank had been knocked out by 
midday. In the north of the Mardakert area, where Karabakh 
subunits are also containing the offensive, another tank has 
been destroyed. There are no reports as yet on manpower losses 
sustained by either side. 
  According to the latest information, a woman was killed in 
yesterday's Azerbaijani air raid on Stepanakert, and two 
children were injured. Some damage was caused. The planes were 
in the air again today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-17245 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov078_r_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-078 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

