<H3> <TI>   Special Envoy Holds Talks With CSCE on Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Special Envoy Holds Talks With CSCE on Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004203094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1858 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Vukolov] </F>
  [Text] Stockholm 20 April TASS -- The Russian president's 
special envoy for Nagorno-Karabakh Vladimir Kazimirov and head 
of the CSCE Minsk group for Nagorno-Karabakh Jan Eliasson held 
here consultations on Karabakh settlement on 19-20 April. 
  The two officials exchanged information on the high-level 
talks and contacts over Nagorno-Karabakh settlement during the 
recent Moscow meeting of the Council of CIS Heads of State, as 
well as on the meeting of the CSCE Minsk group in Prague. 
  Participants in the consultations also exchanged views on 
possible further steps by the Russian mediator and the CSCE 
Minsk group in the Karabakh settlement and around it. They 
stressed the importance of the declaration on Karabakh 
settlement signed in Moscow by the Council of CIS Heads of 
State. Both sides confirmed their commitment to coordinated and 
harmonized mediation efforts. 
  Russia's special envoy and the CSCE official agreed to 
maintain close contacts between the Russian mediation mission 
and the Swedish presidium of the CSCE Minsk group. 
  Kazimirov was received by Swedish Foreign Minister 
Margaretha 
Af Ugglas. 

</TEXT>

