<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Confers With EU Secretary General </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Confers With EU Secretary General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2104170394 Tallinn BNS in English 1455 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2104170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, 21 Apr, BNS -- Estonian Foreign Minister 
Juri Luik met today with Daniel Tarschys, the head of the 
Swedish parliament's foreign commission and the new secretary 
general of the European Union [EU], the Foreign Ministry press 
service told BNS. Tarschys is in Tallinn to attend a meeting of 
parliamentary foreign commissions of the Baltic states, the 
Visegrad states and the Nordic countries. 
  Tarschys affirmed that the European Union will in the next 
few years attach top priority to strengthening the young 
democracies of the central and east European countries. 
  The EU secretary general said expansion of the union is also 
of great importance. In this connection he voiced the opinion 
that a democratic Russia as a member of the EU would be a 
positive development and that just for this reason Russia's 
admission to the union should be conditional upon its fulfilling 
the same requirements as other states. 
  Luik and Tarschys also touched on Estonian-Russian relations 
and the problems connected with the withdrawal of Russian troops 
from Estonia. 

</TEXT>

