<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Additional Peacekeepers Depart for Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Additional Peacekeepers Depart for Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104204994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2037 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 22 April, TASS--Extra Ukrainian peacekeepers 
flew off on Thursday night for the Bosnian capital of Sarajevo. 
  On the eve of its departure, the Ukrainian battalion was 
visited by a group of the Republic's Defence Ministry 
high-ranking officers headed by Lieutenant-General Anatoliy 
Kobzar. According to him, Ukrainian peacekeeping troops 
successfully fulfil their duties in Sarajevo and Bosnia on the 
whole, while the commanders of the Ukrainian battalion are doing 
their utmost to avoid casualties among the republic's 
peacekeepers in the composition of U.N. forces in former 
Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

