<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Considers Withdrawing Troops From Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Considers Withdrawing Troops From Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204104294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1033 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "In case violence escalates on the territory of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina either because of massive NATO air strikes or 
combat activities of the sides directly involved in the conflict 
and (in case of) a threat to the personnel of UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Force], it cannot be ruled out that the question of 
the necessity of further stay of peace-keeping forces in Bosnia 
will arise", Karasin said adding that Yasushi Akashi, the envoy 
of the UN secretary general, had recently mentioned the 
possibility. 
  He stressed that a number of states whose peace-keepers are 
in the zone of conflict had several times noted that in case of 
a real threat to the personnel of their peace-keeping forces the 
question may arise about withdrawing them. 
  Russia will follow suit in this case, according to Karasin. 

</TEXT>

