<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Small Business Sector Increases Output </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Small Business Sector Increases Output </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104105194 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0737 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] Kiev, 20 Apr -- Ukraine's deputy minister of the 
economy, Yuriy Yekhanurov, informed journalists at a meeting of 
the Market Reform Press Club about the results of Ukraine's 
economic activity in the first quarter of this year. He said 
the decline in production amounts to 38.4 percent and 
expenditure from the state budget exceeds income by 5 trillion 
karbovantsi. There are currently 93,100 unemployed persons in 
Ukraine, while so-called hidden unemployment is about 4 million 
persons. He also said that small businesses manufactured 
1.4-times more products in the first quarter of 1994 than in the 
corresponding period of last year. 

</TEXT>

