<H3> <TI>   Government, China Optimistic Over Cooperation Prospects </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government, China Optimistic Over Cooperation Prospects </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104123494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1217 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Glazovskaya] </F>
  [Text] Ashkhabad, 21 April (TASS) -- The first round of 
Turkmen-Chinese summit talks has revealed the identity of their 
stands on the main aspects of cooperation. This was stressed at 
a briefing for journalists, organised by the Chinese side. It 
was stated that Li Peng and Saparmurat Niyazov had expressed 
satisfaction over the level of the development of bilateral 
relations after the establishment of diplomatic contacts in 
1992. Both leaders pointed to mutual understanding and 
confidence, which are typical of the relations between their 
countries. They stressed that there existed a potential for 
their further deepening. 
  It was stated at the briefing that the talks had revealed 
the 
main spheres of possible economic cooperation, of which the 
transportation of Turkmen gas to China is the most important one. 
  Participants in the talks, held in Ashkhabad, pointed out 
that trade turnover between China and Turkenistan is not too 
great so far, but there are chances to make it more effective. 
The Chinese side expressed a lively interest in purchasing 
Turkmen cotton. 
  Four agreements are expected to be signed at the talks, 
which 
will be continued on Friday. They will become more specific 
after a meeting of Chiness business people with heads of Turkmen 
ministries and institutions, scheduled for Friday. 

</TEXT>

