<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets Leaders of `Component' Republics </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Meets Leaders of `Component' Republics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104190994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1729 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 21 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- Today Boris Yeltsin 
had a meeting with leaders of component Russian republics. The 
participants at the meeting expressed support for the prompt 
signing and conscientious implementation of the agreement on 
civic accord, and they adopted a corresponding statement to this 
effect. They noted the importance of constructive cooperation 
between all political forces and all federation subjects to 
solve the problems presently facing the country. 
  The president noted that the present Constitution creates a 
firm basis for the implementation of all natural rights and 
interests of republics without detriment to the unity and 
prosperity of our common fatherland, the Russian Federation. 
Also discussed were the basic principles of the federal 
center's regional strategy and problems of regional policy and 
interregional integration. 
  The participants at the meeting exchanged views on a number 
of economic issues. The president devoted special attention to 
the problem of mutual relations between federal and regional 
bodies of authority in the budgetary sphere, and specified the 
tasks republican leaders face in overcoming the non-payments 
crisis and stabilizing the economic situation. 
  ITAR-TASS was informed of this today by the Russian 
president's press service. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

