<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-078 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104172194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1608 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Boris Yeltsin is meeting with heads of the 
Russian Federation's republics in one of his residences 
southwest of Moscow Thursday. Opening the meeting, Yeltsin 
pointed out that the old tradition of meetings with heads of the 
republics is being revived. "We plan to hold such meetings five 
to seven times a year," he said. "Such a meeting is being held 
for the first time after the adoption of the Constitution and 
elections to the Federal Assembly. In the past months a lot of 
changes have taken place, political stabilization is gaining 
momentum. The ruinous division of power has been overcome." 
  Yeltsin particularly noted that he "practically has no 
differences" with the speakers of the Federal Assembly Chambers 
Ivan Rybkin and Vladimir Shumeyko with whom he has been meeting 
on a regular basis. Yeltsin said that after adopting the 
constitution, new federative relations started to form. Out of 
88 subjects of the Federation, the elections took place and 
"were registered" in 61, and 17 subjects did not gather the 
necessary number of votes. Yeltsin expressed hope that elections 
to local bodies will be fully completed this year. Then a full 
balance of powers will be established, the president noted. 

</TEXT>

