<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Note on Need To Solve Payments Problem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Note on Need To Solve Payments Problem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104115594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1053 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 21 TASS -- "The necessity of solving 
the non-payments problem is one of the main points of the 
memorandum sent by Russian President Boris Yeltsin to Prime 
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and the chairmen of the Federation 
Council and State Duma", presidential spokesman Vycheslav 
Kostikov told a briefing in the Kremlin on Thursday. 
  According to the spokesman, "the technical solution of the 
non-payments problem is the prerogative of the government, but, 
since that question has grown into a political one, it has 
entered the competency of the president". 
  Kostikov said Yeltsin's "memorandum should stimulate the 
process of economic reform". He explained that, in the same 
memorandum, the president "calls the attention of the lawmakers 
to the fact that they have been too slow in enacting laws in the 
economic sphere". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-17285 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov078_b_94014" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-078 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

