<H3> <TI>   Shokhin: Taxes May Be Cut 10-20 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shokhin: Taxes May Be Cut 10-20 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2104122094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 21 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2104122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [POSTFACTUM report: "One-Shot Action To Cut All Taxes </F>
Possible in Fall"] 
  [Text] Aleksandr Shokhin has advised that a one-shot action 
is possible in Russia in fall 1994 cutting back all taxes 10 to 
20 percent which, he thinks, would considerably liven up 
production. He pointed out, however, that this is possible only 
if the money not to be received into the budget is made up for 
from the proposed reserve standby credit ($4 billion) that may 
be received as soon as in the fall. 

</TEXT>

