<H3> <TI>   Foreign Investment Decline in First Quarter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Investment Decline in First Quarter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2104135394 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 21 Apr 94 p I </F>
<F P=103> PM2104135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Own information" report: "Foreign Investment in Russian </F>
Economy Declines in First Quarter" -- from the FINANSOVYYE 
IZVESTIYA section] 
  [Text] According to preliminary figures from the Russian 
State Committee for Statistics [Goskomstat], the growth of 
foreign investment in the Russian economy in the first quarter 
of 1994 came to $290 million -- a decline of 57 percent on the 
fourth quarter of 1993. Investments in joint ventures account 
for around a quarter of all investment. Goskomstat specialists 
note that this year, as in the past, the quarterly dynamics of 
foreign investment inflows into Russia are very irregular. 

</TEXT>

