<H3> <TI>   Stock Exchange President on Privatization Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Stock Exchange President on Privatization Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2104125094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 21 Apr 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK2104125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Vladislav Kuzmichev (NEGA) report in the "Privatization" </F>
column: "The Russian Stock Exchange President Charges Anatoliy 
Chubays. Formation of a New-Type Political Party Begins"] 
  [Text] Yesterday Igor Suvorov, president of the 
joint-stock company Russian Stock Exchange [RSE], held a press 
conference. According to the RSE president, the upcoming 
termination of the circulation of the voucher as a state 
security has provoked special activity by the State Property 
Committee [Goskomimushchestvo], in the person of Anatoliy 
Chubays who, while the privatization program has virtually 
collapsed, is trying to regain the initiative from the Economy 
Ministry and usurp the power to regulate the securities market 
through the infrastructure created by Goskomimushchestvo. 
  The seminar for stock market makers, to be convened on 23 
and 
24 April by the Securities and Stock Exchange Commission under 
the Russian Federation president, in Suvorov's opinion, is in 
fact the beginning of the formation of a new type of political 
party. It is sponsored by the state itself as represented by 
the ministries and departments which have discredited themselves 
in the sphere of privatization. 
  The statement also noted that Mr. Chubays is trying to 
resolve the problem of the enterprise directors corps not on an 
economic basis but by regimenting its activity and assuming the 
function of regulating investment flows. 
  According to the RSE president, the approach that is being 
imposed objectively leads to crime because it envisions a 
multi-stage scenario as a result of which the capital market 
will move from an organized to a cash basis [ot organizovannogo 
k nalichnomy], which corresponds to the interests of shadow 
structures. 

</TEXT>

