<H3> <TI>   Navy's Kasatonov on Status of Battle Training </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Navy's Kasatonov on Status of Battle Training </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104164294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1446 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vasiliy Belousov] </F>
  [Text] Murmansk April 21 TASS -- "If Russia loses her naval 
power, she will lose her status as a great power as well. Our 
navy will, as earlier, serve as the watch-dog of the country", 
first deputy commander-in-chief of Russia's Navy Admiral Igor 
Kasatonov said on Thursday. 
  The admiral, who arrived in Murmansk to participate in the 
northern fleet's military maneuvers, heads the state commission 
on the preparation for the 300-year anniversary of the Russian 
fleet. He emphasised that the Russian fleet was created by the 
whole country, and so the celebration of its anniversary will be 
not a departmental, but a nation-wide event. 
  Speaking about the military readiness of the country's naval 
forces, Admiral Kasatonov said, "the results of the first stage 
of battle training are now being analyzed on all the fleets. On 
the whole, I am satisfied with them. But there are some things 
which need to be worked upon. In particular, we need to give 
our sailors more time on the open sea. I think we will be able 
to correct that problem during the summer", he said. 

</TEXT>

