<F P=102>   LD2204185394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1604 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Belarusian Central Electoral Commission has 
registered 11 initiative groups in support of candidates to 
elections for the first-ever Belarusian president. 
  INTERFAX learned in the central electoral commission that 
among them are groups of Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich; head 
of the former parliamentary commission for combating against 
corruption Aleksandr Lukashenko; ex-speaker of the parliament 
Stanislav Shushkevich; leaders of the Popular Front and the 
Party of Popular Accord Zenon Poznyak and Gennadiy Karpenko; 
President of the Union of Entrepreneurs Vladimir Karyagin; 
General Director of the International Management Institute 
Viktor Tereshchenko; Chairmen of the Association of Invalids and 
the parliamentary commission for economic reform Nikolay 
Kolbasko and Leonid Kozik; Rector of the Commercial University 
Edward Akhrem; and Chairman of the Council of Collective Farms 
Aleksandr Dubko. 
  The central electoral commission denied registration to two 
initiative groups "for including in the list group members 
citizens who did not give their consent." 
  The registration will last until 24 April. 

