<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Signs Statute on Military Service </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Signs Statute on Military Service </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2504083894 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1950 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2504083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to BELAPAN, Colonel General Pavel 
Kazlowski, Belarusian defense minister, signed an order 
activating on 25 April the statute defining conditions for 
contract service by privates, sergeants, sailors, and master 
sergeants in the Belarusian Armed Forces. Thus, all Belarusian 
citizens under 35 years of age who have already been on active 
military service and are still subject to call-up, can sign a 
contract with the Defense Ministry for two years and serve in 
the Army according to their military or civilian profession. 
The same applies to privates and sergeants who are currently 
awaiting transfer to the reserves. Experts estimate that the 
monthly salary of a contract serviceman this April will be about 
390,000 rubles, while a sergeant will make around 509,000 
Belarusian hares. 

</TEXT>

