<DOCNO> FBIS4-17318 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov079_g_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-079 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Said Backing Down on Chernobyl Pledges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Said Backing Down on Chernobyl Pledges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2504075494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1950 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2504075494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Belarusian Party of Labor [BPP] Council has 
issued a statement devoted to the eighth anniversary of the 
catastrophe at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant. It is 
becoming increasingly clear that most of the decisions adopted 
and promises made on this issue by the Republic's leadership 
have not been implemented, the statement said. In the words of 
its authors, many Supreme Soviet deputies, who pledged some time 
ago to free Belarusians of the Chernobyl misery, and the 
government failed to protect people from the Chernobyl radiation 
and drove the people into an economic Chernobyl, bringing them 
to the brink of annihilation. The party council considers it 
inadmissible that the authorities attempt to revise legal acts 
and decisions formerly adopted regarding the protection of 
people from the Chernobyl catastrophe and the level of social 
benefits. The BPP Council calls on all progressive forces to 
rally their efforts aimed at the survival and health of the 
Belarusian people on 26 April, the day of commemoration of the 
Chernobyl tragedy. 

</TEXT>

