<H3> <TI>   Republic Heads Adopt Statement on Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Republic Heads Adopt Statement on Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2504095194 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 23 Apr 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2504095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Heads of Republics Within the </F>
Russian Federation Support It..."] 
  [Text] On 21 April, the Russian president held a meeting 
with the leaders of the republics within the Russian Federation. 
The heads of the republics participating in the meeting adopted 
the following statement: 
  "We participants in the meeting with the Russian Federation 
president, representing the leadership of republics within the 
Russian Federation, aspiring to stability and the affirmation of 
the traditions of dialogue, compromise, and partnership in 
politics, declare our support for the idea of ensuring civil 
peace and accord in our multiethnic country at a crucial stage 
in its history. 
  "Together with the Russian Federation president, we believe 
that the signing of the Agreement on Achieving Civil Accord in 
Russia should demonstrate to Russians that politicians, state 
institutions, and Russian Federation components are capable of 
finding common positions for the effective settlement of urgent 
and socially important tasks within the framework of economic 
and social transformations. Political ambitions, hostility, and 
extremism in federal relations may hinder the quest for a joint 
way out of the crisis, and undermine trust in organs of power at 
all levels. 
  "We appeal to state, political, and social circles in Russia 
to assume responsibility for the stable and consistent 
development of our country, and to become involved in the 
concluding process of the preparation and signing of the 
agreement." 
  dated] Moscow, The Kremlin, 21 April 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

