<F P=100> RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Aide: Yabloko Not to Sign Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Aide: Yabloko Not to Sign Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204174994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1623 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Only one parliamentary faction, Yabloko, will not 
sign the agreement on public accord, presidential aide Georgiy 
Satarov declared at a briefing on Friday in the Kremlin 
commenting on Boris Yeltsin's meeting with representatives of 
Russia's leading political forces. In his words, all other 
factions and parties are looking for their own ways to sign this 
document. 
  Satarov underlined that the working group in charge of the 
preparation of this agreement for signing still receives 
proposals both from political structures and individuals. As he 
said, the final text of the agreement is due to be ready on 
April 26. On April 27 the State Duma will have to pass a 
decision on the text which cannot be changed. 
  Satarov believes that the overwhelming majority of the 
Russia's constituent regions and republics will sign the 
agreement. According to available information, a total of nine 
regions have still not reported about their decision to sign 
this document. 
  Satarov informed journalists about the conversation held 
between Yeltsin and participants of this meeting. He said that 
Yeltsin had declared that his attitude to any group not signing 
this agreement would not change so as to avoid a new spiral of 
confrontation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

