<F P=100> RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar: Civic Accord Agreement Needed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaydar: Civic Accord Agreement Needed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204173594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1404 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An agreement on civil accord should be signed by 
political forces at least for enabling them to resolve political 
differences "through elections, through ballot booths, through 
the press," not through the use of force, the leader of Russia's 
Choice faction in the State Duma Yegor Gaydar told Interfax on 
Friday. 
  A day earlier, during the debates over the signing of the 
agreement in the State Duma Gaydar spoke in favor of its 
signing. In his opinion, the parliamentary majority, which in 
his words, consists of opposition forces should "take 
responsibility for its like-minded persons", because "to provoke 
tensions in Russia today is a strike on security." 
  At the same time, Gaydar acknowledged that the foundation of 
possible civil accord "is very limited and there can be no 
agreement with the opposition on program issues." In 
particular, he pointed to different approaches to private 
property and the restoration of administrative control over the 
economy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

