<H3> <TI>   Agrarian Party Sets Out Conditions for Signing Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agrarian Party Sets Out Conditions for Signing Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404070094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0630 GMT 
24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404070094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Agrarian Party of Russia will sign the agreement 
on public accord only after an agreement is concluded between 
the government and representatives of the agroindustrial 
complex. This agreement ought to guarantee state purchases of 
agricultural produce. This decision was made on 23 April at a 
plenum of the Central Council of the Agrarian Party of Russia. 
It was attended by Chairman of the State Duma Ivan Rybkin, 
Deputy Prime Minister Aleksandr Zaveryukha, and Agriculture 
Minister Viktor Khlystun. 

</TEXT>

