<H3> <TI>   `Working Moscow' Celebrates Lenin Birthday </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Working Moscow' Celebrates Lenin Birthday </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204175094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1618 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2204175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondenbt Igor Belskiy] </F>
  [Excerpt] Moscow, 22 Apr -- The Working Moscow organization 
has declared its intention to "continue lawful counteraction" 
against the Russian authorities at a rally held on the 124th 
anniversary of Vladimir Ilyich Lenin's birthday. A statement by 
the organization's Political Council read out on Moscow's 
Teatralnaya Square today says that it is ready to join the 
agreement on public accord only "on condition that the country's 
present leaders withdraw from the political scene." 
  The organizers of today's mass action are Working Moscow and 
the Russian Communist Workers' Party. Several thousand people 
attended the rally. The slogans and appeals that have become 
traditional at all opposition rallies alternated today with 
attempts to interpret Lenin's activities. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

