<H3> <TI>   Radio Announces May Day Work Holidays </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Announces May Day Work Holidays </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304143594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 
23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] For most people in Russia, there will be four days 
off during the upcoming May Day holiday: Saturday, 30 April; 
and Sunday, Monday, and Tuesday, 1-3 May. 
  In accordance with a government decision, the management of 
any particular enterprise or organization may, in agreement with 
the trade unions, declare 3 May a working day. If citizens work 
on that day, they will receive an additional day off or monetary 
compensation at double time. 
  Nikolay Chishenko, head of the department of labor in the 
government, clarified this for ITAR-TASS. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

