<F P=100> RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Accepts Kazannik's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federation Council Accepts Kazannik's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504103694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0939 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 25 TASS -- The Russian Federation 
Council voted on Monday to accept the resignation of former 
prosecutor general Aleksey Kazannik. 
  121 out of 130 present members of the upper chamber voted 
for 
the decision, four against and five abstained. 
  Kazannik offered to resign in February in connection with 
the 
release of anti-Yeltsin rebels after the State Duma proclaimed a 
political amnesty. 
  Yeltsin accepted the resignation and appointed Aleksey 
Ilyushenko as acting prosecutor general. 
  But Kazannik later changed his mind and the Federation 
Council, which appoints and dismisses the prosecutor, voted to 
reinstate him. 
  To end the crisis Kazannik offered to resign again. 
  The Federation Council now has to discuss the appointment of 
Ilyushenko. Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin was entrusted by 
the president to press for the appointment in the Federation 
Council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

