<H3> <TI>   Moscow TV Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow TV Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304135594 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1100 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Russian Communists said today at an all-Russian 
conference of the Communist Party of the Russian Federation that 
the memorandum on civil accord in its present form is not 
acceptable. Party leader Gennadiy Zyuganov made a speech at the 
conference and said that political measures and not declarations 
should be the basis for civil accord. Their purpose should be 
the elimination of sources of civil confrontation, which he 
believes are the sharp property stratification, the violation of 
social and economic rights of working people, the increase in 
crime, and the spiritual degradation of the public. The head of 
the party believes that a civil accord in Russia is possible but 
it should be agreed upon not by confrontational branches of 
powers but by various political forces. The communists intend 
to set up a wide coalition of left, centrist, and national and 
democratic forces in order to win the elections and to come to 
power legally. 

</TEXT>

