<H3> <TI>   National Salvation Front Urges Early Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Salvation Front Urges Early Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404134794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1238 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Salvation Front [NSF] insists on early 
presidential elections, NSF leader Ilya Konstantinov told his 
organization's National Council in Moscow on Sunday. He said 
that the National Salvation Front would sign the Memorandum on 
Civic Accord only if this demand was fulfilled. 
  Ilya Konstantinov, Gennadiy Sayenko, Mikhail Astafyev and 
Mikhail Titov criticized the Civic Accord pact and announced 
that they would not sign it, although they would take part in 
its discussion on April 26. 
  Konstantinov also said that the NSF's main task now was to 
find and support a candidate representing the opposition. 
  Member of the NSF's Political Council Sazhi Umalatova stated 
that former Soviet prime minister Nikolay Ryzhkov would suit all 
opposition forces. 
  Members of the NSF's National Council sharply criticized the 
government and president. 

</TEXT>

