<H3> <TI>   Calls for Yeltsin's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calls for Yeltsin's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404171094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1534 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Council of the National Salvation Front 
[NSF] adopted a resolution on Sunday which says that Boris 
Yeltsin's resignation is the compulsory condition for signing 
the Civic Accord agreement. 
  The National Council members also expressed protest against 
plans to hold Russian-American manoeuvres in the Orenburg Region 
(the Urals) and urged all patriots to join this protest. 
  Ilya Konstantinov was elected chairman of the NSF's 
Executive 
Committee. 
  Four more co-chairmen were elected in addition to the 17 
already working: Sazhiy Umalatova, Valeriy Skurlatov, Mikhail 
Titov and Valeriy Smirnov. 

</TEXT>

