<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thousands Join Kazannik's People's Conscience Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Thousands Join Kazannik's People's Conscience Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404085394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0807 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Petrov] </F>
  [Text] Omsk April 24 TASS -- Several thousand people have 
joined the People's Conscience Party which Alexey Kazannik, 
former prosecutor-general of Russia, is founding upon his 
returning here. 
  Kazannik is again a profesor at the law department of Omsk 
University. He devotes all his spare time to the elaboration of 
programmatic documents and organisational structure of the new 
party. 
  More than 5,000 people have joined the party within three 
days in Yekaterinburg, the hometown of President Boris Yeltsin, 
Kazannik told ITAR-TASS. The most active support in forming the 
party is being given by scientists and faculty members of 
Novosibirsk and Omsk institutions of higher learning, the 
Academgorodok (science city) and other cities in Siberia, the 
Urals and the Far East, by entrepreneurs and the work 
collectives of industrial enterprises. 
  Kazannik said he was prompted to found a party of his own by 
"the immorality and inefficiency of the present authorities at 
all levels and by the impossibility to combine efforts with all 
the already existing parties and movements for moral 
considerations". 

</TEXT>

