<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Styazhkin] </F>
  [Text] Pyatigorsk, Stavropol Territory, April 24 TASS -- 
"We insist that the president, the government and the Federal 
Assembly of Russia immediately take measures to adjust taxation 
policy, streamline managerial bureaucracy, resolutely curb crime 
and ensure strict compliance with laws", said a statement issued 
here by participants in a visiting session of the Union of 
Entrepreneurs and Lease-Holders of the Russian Federation. 
  The members of the union drew attention to the urgent 
necessity to increase efforts to combat crime also because, in 
their view, a large proportion of the population come to view 
entrepereneurs -- the main taxpayers -- as a mafia-like corrupt 
set. 
