<F P=100> RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kokoshin Urges Financial-Industrial Conglomerates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kokoshin Urges Financial-Industrial Conglomerates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2304092094 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 23 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> MK2304092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Own correspondent's report: "Andrey Kokoshin: Robust </F>
Economy and Industry Are the Foundation of Russian National 
Security"] 
  [Text] Russia's national security should be founded on a 
developed economy with a robust financial system, Andrey 
Kokoshin, first deputy defense minister, stressed in his address 
at the Fourth Congress of the Russian Commercial Banks 
Association. He pointed out the need to accelerate the process 
of setting up formidable financial-industrial groups in Russia 
and the CIS in order to manufacture science-intensive industrial 
products for both civilian and military purposes that will be 
competitive on the world market. 
  The creation of financial-industrial groups will make it 
possible considerably to ease pressure on the government budget 
and to boost investment in industry. Back in 1991, Andrey 
Kokoshin, who headed a group of economists, historians, and 
industrialists at the time, put forward the initiative to create 
such groups and powerful companies drawing on rich foreign 
experience. The main elements of these "locomotives" of the 
domestic economy would be enterprises of the former USSR's 
military-industrial sector that are undergoing conversion to 
civilian uses and diversifying their area of expertise. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

