<F P=100> RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pensioners To Receive New Benefits 1 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pensioners To Receive New Benefits 1 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204131594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1147 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Luidmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 22 TASS -- The State Duma, the Russian 
parliament's lower chamber, endorsed on Friday the government's 
bill on state pensions. According to the bill, a minimum monthly 
pension benefit in Russia is fixed at 19 thousand roubles from 
May 1 and all other pension benefits will be increased 1.3 
times. Inflation compensation of 19700 roubles will be paid in 
addition to pension benefits as before. The difference between 
maximum and minimum benefits will increase twofold (comparing to 
1.85 times at present). 
  The bill, which is also to be approved by the Federation 
Council, the upper chamber, will provide the adjustment of 
pensions to the price growth, taking into account the financial 
resourses of the pension fund. In spite of many critical 
remarks and proposals, the lawmakers decided to endorse the bill 
allowing the payment of new benefits to begin from May 1, but 
the work to improve the pension laws will continue. However, 
some proposals, including on the government's power to fully 
regulate pensions, were withdrawn from the bill. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

