<H3> <TI>   Cosmos-2278 Satellite Launched From Baykonur </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cosmos-2278 Satellite Launched From Baykonur </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304110994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1052 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Semyon Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 23 TASS -- The Cosmos-2278 satellite 
was launched from the Baykonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan at 
11.02, Moscow time, on Saturday. The launching was carried out 
by the Space Armed Forces in the interests of the Russian 
Defence Ministry. 
  The satellite was put into orbit by a Zenit-2 
rocket-booster. 
  This was the first launching of a rocket of this type and 
the 
22nd since the first firing-off in April, 1985, a spokesman for 
the Space Armed Forces told ITAR-TASS. 
  The Cosmos-2278 satellite is the 1075th spacecraft launched 
from the Baykonur Cosmodrome. The first one was put into orbit 
on October 4, 1957. 

</TEXT>

