<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Semen Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 25 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- The Cosmos-2278 
artificial Earth satellite launched yesterday by the Russian 
military-space forces from the Baykonur cosmodrome has been 
placed in an orbit with the following parameters: period of 
revolution: 102.0 minutes, orbital inclination: 70.99 degrees, 
apogee: 880.78 km, perigee: 851.95 km. The satellite was 
launched by a Zenit-2 rocket-launcher. 
  ITAR-TASS was told at the Russian military space forces that 
Cosmos-2278 is the 1,075th satellite launched from Baykonur in 
the 37 years of its history. 

