<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Condolences on Chernobyl Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Condolences on Chernobyl Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204185694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1737 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin addressed the nation 
on the occasion of the eighth anniversary of the Chernobyl 
disaster. He said that April 26 was a day of mourning to those 
who died in radiation emergencies and disasters. 
  He paid homage to those who were exposed to radiation while 
fighting the disaster. He said that the country would not 
forget those who were still living in areas contaminated by 
nuclear radiation. 
  In an address released by the presidential press service 
Yeltsin said April 26 was a day when the danger of nuclear 
disasters was especially obvious and that everything had to be 
done to make the world a safer place. 
  "On the day when Russia bows its head in memory of those who 
died in radiation disasters I express my deep condolences to the 
Russians and citizens of other countries whose relatives and 
friends fell in a fight with a deadly force and shielded us from 
disaster," the address says. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

