<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Denies Plans for Khabarovsk Plant </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Denies Plans for Khabarovsk Plant </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2304083094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 23 Apr 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK2304083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "In Brief" rubric] </F>
  [Text] Khabarovsk -- "There are no plans at the moment to 
build any underground or surface nuclear electric-power stations 
on the territory of Khabarovsk Kray," Nikolay Balyukin, general 
director of the "Khabarovskenergo" joint-stock company said, 
commenting on reports of the supposed construction together with 
Japan of an underground nuclear electric-power station in the 
area of Komsomolsk-na-Amure. In his words, the discussions 
conducted in past years about the possible construction of a 
nuclear station in the area of Lake Emoron ended in the decision 
that a return to the question is possible only after serious 
scientific studies and the holding of a referendum among the 
population. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

