<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Arrives in Bishkek, Met by Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Arrives in Bishkek, Met by Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204161594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1511 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Mainayev] </F>
  [Text] Bishkek 22 April TASS -- Chinese Premier Li Peng 
began his official visit to Kyrgyzstan on Friday [22 April]. 
The guest arrived from Ashkhabad [Ashgabat] to Bishkek in the 
evening, and was met by Kyrgyzstan President Askar Akayev, Prime 
Minister Apas Amumagulov and other officials in the "Manas" 
airport. Then the motorcade proceeded to the suburban 
governmental residence "Ala-Archa." 
  Among the items included in Li Peng's three-day visit are 
meetings with the leadership of Kyrgyzstan and the signing of 
several inter-governmental agreements on commercial and cultural 
cooperation. These documents are designed to strengthen the 
already significant legal basis for bilateral relations between 
the two countries. They have already signed approximately 40 
treaties, agreements and protocols in the last two years. 
  President Askar Akayev visited Beijing in January 1993. Li 
Peng's return visit, planned for that spring, was delayed due to 
his health problems. 

</TEXT>

