<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akayev, Li Peng `Deeply Satisfied' With Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Akayev, Li Peng `Deeply Satisfied' With Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304100794 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0930 GMT 23 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kyrgyz President Askar Akayev and Chinese Prime 
Minister Li Peng are deeply satisfied with the level, prospects, 
and dynamics of the development of bilateral relations, Imar 
Rasaliyev, the Kyrgyz president's press secretary, said at a 
briefing in Bishkek today. He was speaking about the results of 
talks between the leaders of the two countries. In particular, 
he noted a certain degree of progress achieved in discussing the 
issue of disputed territories between Kyrgyzstan and China. 

</TEXT>

