<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government `Satisfied' With Talks With Opposition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government `Satisfied' With Talks With Opposition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104173994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1517 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe 21 April TASS -- Tajik Labor and Employment 
Minister Shukyrdzhon Zukhurov, who heads the Dushanbe 
governmental delegation to the negotiations with the Tajik 
opposition, said he was satisfied with the first round of talks. 
He stressed that, despite different approaches to several 
questions, the two sides had taken the first step towards a 
political solution to the inter-Tajik national conflict. 
  Zukhurov told a press-conference on Thursday that the 
difficult two-week negotiations had started 5 April in Moscow 
upon the initiative of the United Nations and with the 
participation of observers from several nearby republics, 
including Iran, Afghanistan and Pakistan. The two sides looked 
at three groups of questions concerning the necessity of 
bringing a halt to hostilities on the Tajik-Afghan border and 
inside Tajikistan itself. 
  A protocol on the return of refugees and a general 
communique 
on the results of the first round were signed at the round's 
finish. The head of the governmental delegation said that the 
second round had been scheduled for approximately the end of May 
and would be held in either Tehran or Islamabad. 

</TEXT>

