<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khamchiyev: Ossetians `Aiming for Mass Bloodshed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khamchiyev: Ossetians `Aiming for Mass Bloodshed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204233594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1654 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2204233594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 22 Apr -- Belan Khamchiyev, the permanent 
representative of the Ingush Republic under the Russian 
president, told the ITAR-TASS correspondent that the latest 
events on the border of the two republics once again prove that 
the Ossetian side is aiming for mass bloodshed. According to 
him, North Ossetia is shutting off all prospects for the 
negotiation process. 
  In the situation that has emerged, Khamchiyev believes the 
entire responsibility for the failure of the latest round of 
negotiations between the leaders of the two republics rests upon 
the top leaders of North Ossetia and Russia. Given that all 
possible means for a peaceful settlement have been virtually 
exhausted, it is expedient at the next sitting of the Federation 
Council to consider the question of introducing amendments to 
the Russian president's decree on introducing a state of 
emergency and to introduce direct federal rule on the territory 
of Prigorodnyy Rayon. 

</TEXT>

