<H3> <TI>   Electricity Off Throughout Chechen Republic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electricity Off Throughout Chechen Republic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204131194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1027 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Staff workers under the Chechen president told 
INTERFAX that Thursday night electricity was switched off 
throughout the Republic. Friday morning power remained to be 
restored. 
  They assumed the Russian joint stock society United Power 
System moved to punish the Chechen Republic for its failure to 
square a 12.5-billion ruble debt for electrical power and an 
8-billion ruble debt for the delivery of natural gas. 

</TEXT>

