<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Signs Cooperation Treaty with Dagestan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Signs Cooperation Treaty with Dagestan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2504093794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 23 Apr 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2504093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from the ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, ITAR-TASS column: </F>
"Moscow Extends Hand"] 
  [Text] An agreement on cooperation in the economic, 
scientific, technical, and sociocultural spheres has been 
concluded between the governments of Dagestan and Moscow. The 
agreement was signed during the course of a visit here by a 
delegation from the Russian capital headed by Mayor Yuriy 
Luzhkov. 
  The delegation visited a number of cities in the republic, 
familiarized itself with the economy, toured construction 
projects, and visited the Caspian "Dagdizel" Plant, where a 
discussion was held on the enterprise's potential, the problems 
of conversion, and opportunities for cooperation with Moscow 
plants. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

