<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Says Pacific Border District Combat-Ready </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General Says Pacific Border District Combat-Ready </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504065494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0630 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504065494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Leonid Vinogradov and Yuriy </F>
Grachev] 
  [Text] Vladivostok April 25 TASS -- The commander of 
Russian border troops, Colonel-General Andrey Nikolayev, 
completed an inspection tour of Russian Pacific frontiers. 
After his visit to Sakhalin, Kamchatka and the maritime 
territory, he firmly said that Russian border guards are fully 
combat-capable. 
  Nikolayev held consultations with maritime territory head 
Yevgeniy Nazdratenko on strengthening cooperation between border 
troops and civil population to guard natural resources. 
  Nazdratenko stressed at the meeting that it is high time to 
put an end to the pillage of the Russian Far East: Chinese 
poachers rapaciously pick up jinseng in the Ussurian Taiga, 
while Japanese, Polish, Chinese, North and South Korean 
fishermen illegally fish in the Russian sea economic zone. 
  However, the first days of the poach-control dragnet have 
shown that, apart from foreigners, Russian fishermen are also 
guilty of rapacious attitude to natural resources. The 
coastguard service detained several Russian ships which had no 
fishing licences. 
  Nikolayev departed for Khabarovsk on Monday. 

</TEXT>

