<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliamentary Elections Unnecessary in Cherkessk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliamentary Elections Unnecessary in Cherkessk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404200194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1944 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Styazhkin] </F>
  [Text] Cherkessk April 24 TASS -- Elections to the people's 
assembly of the North Caucasian republic of 
Karachayevo-Cherkessiya, scheduled for Sunday, became 
unnecessary. The People's Assembly, which was designed to 
radically transform the republic's legislative power, has been 
already formed: This name was assumed by the republican 
parliament under a decision taken by its session. 
  Official elections to the People's Assembly will be held 
after Karachayevo-Cherkessiya passes its constitution. It is to 
be drafted by the National Council and then submitted for the 
people's discussion. 
  The same decision by the parliament made unnecessary a 
republican referendum also scheduled for Sunday. Put to 
people's vote was the question about the need for presidency in 
Karachayevo-Cherkessiya. When passed, the constitution will 
solve this problem. 
  Primarily, the decision to hold elections to the People's 
Assembly and a referendum in the republic was taken by the 
republican parliament last year. But then it was revised at the 
initiative of the republic's major political parties and mass 
movements which decided that it would be difficult to build 
truly effective bodies of government without a constitution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

