<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    By-Election to Altay Local Legislature Valid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404141294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1349 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valentin Pavlov] </F>
  [Text] Barnaul April 24 TASS -- Elections to the local 
legislative assembly were rerun on Sunday in nine constituencies 
of the Altay territory in southern Siberia. 
  As of 18:00 local time, turnout in the town of Rubtsovsk 
made 
up 34 per cent, in the regional capital Barnaul -- 28 per cent 
and in the city of Biysk -- 27 per cent. Thus, all 50 deputies 
have been already elected to the local legislature, and today's 
polls can be declared valid. 

</TEXT>

