<H3> <TI>   Chuvashia President Announces Reform Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chuvashia President Announces Reform Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304140894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1307 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valentina Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Cheboksary April 23 TASS -- President of Chuvashia, 
a republic in the Volga region, Nikolay Fedorov, announced on 
Saturday his programme of popular reform in the republic. 
  The programme prioritises steady state support for 
manufacturers and small businesses, effective investment policy 
and establishment of an economic and social infrastructure. 
  Fedorov believes that the implementation of his programme 
will hinge on "professional cooperation with the federal 
authorities of the Russian Federation," Russian constituent 
republics and CIS states, as well as neighbouring regions and 
all ethnic communities living inside and outside Chuvashia. 

</TEXT>

