<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Modernization of Petersburg Airport Completed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Modernization of Petersburg Airport Completed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2204141194 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 22 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2204141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Sergey Krayukhin report: "Modernized Pulkovo-2 Airport Up </F>
to International Standards"] 
  [Text] St. Petersburg -- The modernization of Pulkovo-2, 
Russia's second airport in terms of importance and size, is 
complete. 
  The cost of the work, which began four years ago, has been 
estimated at $14 million. The modernization of the airport and 
its terminal was paid for by the "Pulkovo" aviation enterprise, 
which did not take a single kopek from the city budget. The 
modernization of Pulkovo-2 will make it possible not only to 
improve the quality of passenger services but also considerably 
to increase the airport's handling capacity. St. Petersburg now 
has direct flights to 27 cities in Europe and can cope with a 
maximum of 5 million passengers a year. Meanwhile the airport's 
increased capacity will be sufficient for three years. The 
construction of Pulkovo-3, a major new airport on the banks of 
the Neva, will begin in 1997. 

</TEXT>

