<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Apr 22, BNS -- Lithuanian and Kazakh 
officials on Thursday [21 April] completed talks on legal 
assistance and legal relations in civil, family and criminal 
cases. The final round of talks was held in Kazakhstan's 
capital Almaty. 
  Lithuanian Deputy Minister of Justice Ginataras Svedas and 
his Kazakh counterpart Sergey Tikhonov initialed a bilateral 
agreement on mutual legal assistance. 

</TEXT>

