<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Envoy Presents Gore Letter to Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Envoy Presents Gore Letter to Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2204200394 Tallinn BNS in English 1906 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2204200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Apr 22, BNS -- Latvian Prime Minister Valdis 
Birkavs received U.S. Ambassador Ints Silins who handed over a 
letter from his country's Vice President Al Gore, the Government 
Information Agency (VIA) told BNS on Friday [22 April]. 
  Silins reiterated the unambiguous support of the U.S. 
Administration for the March 15 initialed agreements on Russian 
troop withdrawal. The signing of the documents would allow 
international organizations to involve in the control of their 
implementation, Silins said. 
  Silins reconfirmed the United States' commitment to allot 2 
million dollars to dismantle the new building of the Russian- 
operated radar facility at Skrunda as soon as the withdrawal 
package is signed. 
  VIA failed to inform BNS about the content of Al Gore's 
letter but presumably it contains the same idea as Silins said. 

</TEXT>

