<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   GATT Membership Conditions Discussed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GATT Membership Conditions Discussed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2204153494 Riga LETA in English 1152 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2204153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga LETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, 22 April (LETA) -- Thursday [21 April] in the 
Latvian Foreign Ministry a news conference was held by the 
leader of a GATT working group, Finn Teilgard, who visits Riga 
to discuss the conditions of Latvia entering this organization 
with the Latvian Administration. In the course of his visit he 
met the Latvian prime minister, Valdis Birkavs, the Saeima's 
[parliament] chairman, Anatolijs Gorbunovs, and some Latvian 
ministers and experts. 
  Mr. Teilgard said that he told the Latvian Government about 
the six basic principles of this organization which is mainly 
purposed for the promotion of international cooperation and the 
development of trade among its 124 member country. The first 
condition providing the participation in GATT is that Latvia has 
to work out the memorandum on the state political and economic 
situations plus the documents reflecting the current external 
trade procedure in the country and send them to the GATT 
headquarters. 
  The leadership of GATT shows its understanding of the 
present 
economic situation in Latvia, and will take it into account when 
the issue of Latvia's participation in GATT is under discussion, 
Mr. Teilgard said. 

</TEXT>

