<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Talks With EU Team </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Talks With EU Team </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2204153594 Riga LETA in English 1152 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2204153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga LETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, 22 April (LETA) -- The focal point of the 
meeting of the Latvian Government's head, Valdis Birkavs, with 
the delegation of the European Union [EU] was what issues Latvia 
wishes to discuss at the conference in Paris scheduled for late 
May and dedicated to the European stability pact. 
  The governmental information agency reports that Valdis 
Birkavs confirmed his willingness to take an active part in the 
European stability pact. Speaking on the issues Latvia would 
like to consider during the coming conference in Paris, the 
prime minister said Latvia is interested to involve into the 
discussion with other countries of the issues of national 
identity preserving, national minorities' integration into a 
society and teaching a state language. 
  Latvia would wish to view the possibility of launching the 
ombudsman institution. The issue of the repatriation of Russian 
military retirees is of the same importance and needs 
consideration in the context of the stability pact. All these 
matters Latvia would like to discuss at the multilateral talks. 
  Mentioning the issue of the borders with Russia, Birkavs 
expressed doubt whether it is comprehensive to discuss the issue 
at the coming conference and stressed the fact that Latvia is 
forming its stand basing upon the peace pact of 1920 between the 
two states. 

</TEXT>

