  [Text] President Geydar Aliyev received Foreign Minister 
Hikmet Cetin and his delegation today. After welcoming the 
visiting delegation, President Aliyev briefed the Turkish 
diplomats on the social and political developments in 
Azerbaijan. Referring to the fighting in Azerbaijan, Aliyev 
said that while Armenia's aggression against the republic has 
intensified, Azerbaijan's people hoped that the countries around 
the world, particularly Turkey, would take resolute steps to end 
the aggression. However, Aliyev said: Regrettably, regarding 
the UN resolutions and the CSCE effort, a satisfactory outcome 
is impossible. This is because Armenia's aggression, which has 
continued for six years, [words indistinct]. An effective 
solution cannot be [words indistinct]. 
  Foreign Minister Cetin said that Turkey cannot be reconciled 
with a country that occupies Azerbaijan's territory. He also 
noted that Turkey will always support Azerbaijan's efforts to 
defend its territory. 
  Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov, First Deputy Prime Minister 
Fuad Sharipov, State Advisers [name indistinct] and Vefa 
Gulizade, and Altan Karamanoglu, Turkey's ambassador to 
Azerbaijan, attended the meeting. 

