<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Forces Shoot Down Azeri Bomber </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karabakh Forces Shoot Down Azeri Bomber </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304172994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1614 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Nagorno-Karabakh Defense Ministry press service 
told Interfax that the Karabakh air-defense forces had shot down 
a SU-25 Azerbaijani jet which had tried to bomb Stepanakert (the 
capital of Nagorno-Karabakh). A total of seven Azerbaijani jets 
had taken part in the air attack, Stepanakert said. 
  However, the Azerbaijani Defense Ministry announced that an 
Azerbaijani jet had suffered a clash on April 23 when carrying 
out a regular training flight. The pilot baled out and was 
saved, Baku affirmed. 

</TEXT>

