<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conflicting Reports on Fighting in Nagorno-Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conflicting Reports on Fighting in Nagorno-Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404143194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 
24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the Defense Ministry of Azerbaijan, 
last night Armenian troops launched an offensive on the Terter 
and Geranboy directions in the north of Nagorno-Karabakh, but 
suffered heavy losses and failed to achieve any significant 
success. 
  Meanwhile, completely opposite reports are coming from 
Armenian sources. According to a statement by the press service 
of the staff of the defense army of Nagorno-Karabakh, this 
morning Azerbaijani troops went on to the offensive in the 
Fizulinskiy [Fizuli] and Mardakertskiy [Mardakert] Rayons, but 
all their attacks were repelled and on several sections the 
Karabakh detachments managed to seize strategic heights. 
  The Armenian side also reports large losses suffered by the 
enemy in today's fighting. These were INTERFAX and RIA reports. 

</TEXT>

