<F P=102>   NC2304195594 Baku TURAN in English 1723 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2304195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, April 23 (TURAN) -- "Azeri President Geydar 
Aliyev has been forced to postpone his visit to Brussels due to 
the escalation of Armenian aggression", said the Presidential 
apparat's press-service. The visit, which was planned on April 
26, was put off for a week. 
  During the visit, Azerbaijan's participation in NATO's 
programme, "Partnership for the sake of peace", will be 
discussed. 
  Last week, during the press-conference, Azeri Foreign 
Minister Gasan Gasanov told journalists that "the possibility of 
Azerbaijan's joining the NATO programme is being reviewed by the 
Azeri Government and Azerbaijan will give its final answer in 
the near future. 

</TEXT>

