<H3> <TI>   Alliance of National-Democratic Parties Created </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alliance of National-Democratic Parties Created </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2304204994 Baku TURAN in English 1723 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2304204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, April 23 (TURAN)--Yesterday the parties of 
"Boz Gurd", United Azerbaijan, Young Azerbaijan and the 
Azerbaijan National-Democratic Party created the alliance of 
National-Democratic parties. 
  "The goal of the alliance is to mobilize all forces of the 
nation to withstand Armenian's aggression, to safeguard 
territorial integrity and Azeri borders, to protect human 
rights, principles of democracy, and the traditions and culture 
of the Azeri nation", according to the mission of the alliance 
that was read at a press conference. 
  Representatives of the parties criticized the internal and 
external policy of the current leadership of the country. 
  "The staff appointment policy of the Azeri leadership is 
based on bribery", said the Chairman of "Boz Gurd" party, 
Bakhtiyar Akhmedov. 
  According to Iskander Gamidov, "Alliance differs from the 
Democratic Congress, other blocs and democratic parties. It 
gives first priority to the national problem." 
  He mentioned that the alliance is in opposition to the Azeri 
leadership. He said that the Alliance will protest all acts 
that run counter to the national interests of Azerbaijan will be 
submitted to the interests of other countries. [sentence as 
received] 

</TEXT>

