<H3> <TI>   Crackdown on Terrorism, Corruption Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crackdown on Terrorism, Corruption Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204190194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1737 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting between the parliamentary leadership 
and law-enforcement officials in Tbilisi Friday, Georgian leader 
Eduard Shevardnadze announced the beginning of a crackdown on 
terrorism and corruption. "Neither I nor the security service 
will rest until we catch the murderer of Deputy Interior 
Minister Giya Gulua," he was quoted as saying. 
  Shevardnadze called corruption "the biggest danger facing 
the 
country." He added that "it will devour all Georgia, and dreams 
of democracy will remain a fairy tale." 
  Shevardnadze instructed the Interior Ministry, security 
service, prosecutor's and judicial bodies and the whole 
government to develop a draft decree on tighter corruption 
controls, including specific tasks, within ten days. 

</TEXT>

