<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze, Local Administration Heads Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze, Local Administration Heads Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404143794 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1300 
GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian head of state held a meeting with the 
heads of local administrations of Georgia yesterday. The 
meeting was opened by Teimuraz Pipia, head of the directorate of 
regional management, who considered problems of all rayons in 
one context. 
  Zurab Gegechkori [chairman of the state committee on land 
resources] spoke about the process of privatization. He said 
there were numerous problems in the issue of distributing land 
and moot problems pertaining to land issues that existed in 
relations between rayons had to be settled. He also pointed out 
there were instances of unlawful seizure of lands. 
  Next to take floor was Georgian Education Minister Tamaz 
Kvachantiradze, who spoke about problems pertaining to the 
system of education in rayons. He said salaries of school 
teachers had been considerably increased. Teachers working full 
time will earn 900,000 coupons [per month]. It was added that a 
promotion like this granted to teachers would not solve all 
problems existing in the system of education. The minister 
requested assistance from the heads of rayon administrations. 
  Other problems of rayons were also given consideration at 
the 
meeting. 
  In conclusion, Eduard Shevardnadze, Georgian head of state, 
made a speech. He made an appraisal of the meeting and set 
appropriate tasks and instructions for the heads of rayon 
administrations. 

</TEXT>

