<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Cancels Duties on Georgian Goods </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Cancels Duties on Georgian Goods </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304095094 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0800 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to SAKINPORM, Georgia's customs department 
has received a letter from the Customs Committee of the Russian 
Federation signed by Kruglyakov, first deputy chairman of the 
committee. The letter says: Because the Republic of Georgia 
has been a member of the CIS since 1 March 1994, in accordance 
with the edict issued by the Russian Federation Customs 
Committee, the heads of its regional departments and customs 
houses have been officially instructed not to levy a tax in the 
form of VAT, special duties, and excise duties on goods produced 
in Georgia and carried from the Georgian territory retroactive 
to 1 March 1994. Money already paid for the above-mentioned 
taxes should be refunded from the customs house account or it 
can be applied to future payments. 

</TEXT>

