<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rukh Leader Comments on Russian Position </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rukh Leader Comments on Russian Position </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304163494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1322 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian fleet is significant and it must be 
based in Sevastopol, People's RUKh [Ukrainian People's Movement 
for Perestroyka] leader, Vyacheslav Chornovil, told 
INTERFAX-Ukraine. 
  He said if Ukraine had to share with somebody military bases 
and a part of the fleet this must be carried out under generally 
recognized international principles. 
  Chornovil estimated the Ukrainian position at the talks as 
"the only right one." He considered the conduct of Russian 
Defense Minister Pavel Grachev as improper. Chornovil said this 
had once again manifested the "boorishness of a superpower." 
  He suggested that Russia's position at the talks had 
reflected its gradual pro-imperial policy. 
  Given that the U.S. possess "certain influence" and are 
interested in normalization of Russian-Ukrainian relations the 
U.S. mediation in settlement of the Black Sea Fleet issue could 
be useful, Chornovil said. 
  "Grachev would hardly slam the door if there were a U.S. 
representative at the talks," Chornovil suggested. 
  He said in Kravchuk's place he would have addressed the 
Russian president to make him show "his ministers their place." 
"A kind of demarche is definitely needed. Such an offense 
should not be ignored," Chornovil added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

