<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Continuation of Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Continuation of Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Defense Ministry Releases Statement </H4>

<F P=102> LD2204172194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1500 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2204172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The press service of the Ukrainian Defense Ministry 
today denied Moscow's ITAR-TASS report that the position of the 
Ukrainian side at the negotiations in Sevastopol allegedly did 
not correspond with the spirit of constructiveness 
characteristic of the approach of the Russian side to the 
negotiations, and also that representatives of the Ukrainian 
Defense Ministry and Navy were allegedly trying to disavow the 
Moscow agreement of 15 April. 
  The Defense ministry press service also stated that the 
ITAR-TASS report does not conform to reality and that some of 
the mass media distorted the undeniable fact that the Black Sea 
Fleet belongs to two states, rather than to Russia alone. 
  As for the reference to the fact that the position of the 
Ukrainian side with regard to a Ukrainian Navy base in 
Sevastopol contravenes military theory, the Defense Ministry 
press service is authorized to state that Ukraine has its own 
military doctrine and follows its requirements aimed at ensuring 
state independence. 

</TEXT>

