<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Continuation of Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Continuation of Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Radetskyy Talks Break Off </H4>

<F P=102> LD2204201994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2001 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Stetsyuk -- TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol 22 April TASS -- Ukrainian Defence 
Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy described as a complete surprise the 
behaviour of the Russian defence minister who did not return to 
negotiations on gradual settlement of the Black Sea Fleet 
problem after the break. 
  In the opinion of Radetskyy, the negotiations started rather 
successfully and the sides reached an essential agreement on the 
fleet division under which Russia will get over 600 units and 
ukraine -- over 150. 
  Speaking of basing of the Russian Black Sea Fleet and the 
Ukrainian Navy, Radetskyy said the Russian side offered 
conditions unacceptable for Ukraine, under which all Crimean 
bases shall be kept by Russia. 
  He said they are ready to discuss compromise variants and 
there were no reasons to break the dialogue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

