<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Continuation of Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Continuation of Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Parties Outline Ways To Solve Problems </H4>

<F P=102> LD2304161694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1322 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The press center of the Black Sea Fleet command 
declared that in the course of the next round of the 
Russian-Ukrainian negotiations on the Black Sea Fleet held 21-22 
April in Sevastopol the parties "have outlined the ways to solve 
the problems under discussion." The information of the press 
center stresses that the participants of the dialogue recognize 
that "the Black Sea Fleet should not become an apple of discord 
between the friendly states." 
  "At the same time we should admit that the position of the 
Ukrainian party did not meet the spirit of constructiveness with 
which the Russian delegation has come to the negotiations." 
"There was an impression that representatives of Ukraine's 
Defense Ministry and Navy try to disavow the Moscow agreement 
dated 15 April 1994 another time," says the message. 
  The press center believes that "the Ukrainian party admits 
dual interpretation of the provisions of the Moscow agreement on 
separate basing of two fleets and proportional division of the 
Black Sea Fleet. To this effect it refers to the fact that as 
before representatives of Ukraine's Defense Ministry "insist 
that Ukraine's Black Sea Fleet and Navy should be stationed in 
Sevastopol." The authors of this document assert that "this 
contradicts not only to the logic of the military theory but to 
the will of the Russian and Ukrainian presidents and to the last 
decisions of the Sevastopol city council of people's deputies." 
  The document underlines that "the Russian delegation hopes 
that sound sense would prevail over political ambitions and the 
negotiations would continue." "The Russian party takes off the 
entire responsibility for the disruption of a constructive 
dialogue," declared the press center of the Black Sea Fleet. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

