<DATE1>  24 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Republican Party Wants Elections Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Republican Party Wants Elections Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504101494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The holding of elections for president of Ukraine 
and the chairmen and deputies of local councils in June is 
extremely undesirable and dangerous for the fate of Ukraine. 
Ukrainian Republican Party Chairman Mykhaylo Horyn said this at 
a news conference devoted to the results of the party's 
extraordinary congress. 
  The Ukrainian Republican Party leader stressed that the 
elections should take place after a new Ukrainian constitution 
or a law on power is adopted. At the same time Mykhaylo Horyn 
emphasized that, as postponing the elections is problematical, 
the [party] congress gave the Ukrainian Republican Party 
leadership the right to take a stand on its attitude to 
contenders for the post of president of Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

