<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Satisfied With Elections, Voices Concern Over Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Satisfied With Elections, Voices Concern Over Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2204104594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1000 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2204104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As a European Union [EU] communique on the 
Ukrainian elections says, the EU with pleasure and enthusiasm 
assumes that the elections were free and legal. This has been 
confirmed by observers' reports, in which they praise the 
organizational efforts. The EU expects that the election results 
will allow Ukraine to continue political and economic reforms. 
The EU has voiced concern over increasing tensions in the 
Crimea. It fully supports Ukraine's territorial integrity, 
according to the UN Charter and the principles of the CSCE Final 
Act. 

</TEXT>

