<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plyushch Says All Republics Should Share Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Plyushch Says All Republics Should Share Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204131394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1222 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Melnik -- TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 22 April TASS -- the Black Sea Fleet should be 
shared by all former Soviet republics, Speaker of the Ukrainian 
Parliament Ivan Plyushch said on Friday. 
  "From the very beginning the Black Sea Fleet was shared in 
the wrong way," he told a press conference. 
  According to Plyushch, the "zero option" of sharing the 
fleet 
would have settled many problems, including the Crimean one. 
  In the meantime, the Russian and Ukrainian defence ministers 
are currently discussing in Sevastopol how to share the fleet 
between the two countries. Russia wants to have 85 per cent of 
the fleet and leave 15 per cent to Ukraine. Kiev disagrees and 
insists on 20 and more per cent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

