<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Justice Minister `Shocked' by Meshkov's Decisions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Justice Minister `Shocked' by Meshkov's Decisions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2204135194 Kiev KIEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI in Russian 21 Apr 94 p 
3 </F>

<F P=103> WS2204135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev KIEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Natalya Ishchenko: "Meshkov Cannot Be </F>
Rationalized"] 
  [Text] Ukrainian Minister of Justice Vasyl Onopenko was 
shocked by last morning's reports that Crimean President Yuriy 
Meshkov dismissed Crimean Justice Minister Yevhen Skisov by 
virtue of another decree. "I simply do not understand Mr. 
Meshkov," Vasyl Onopenko said in an interview with KIEVSKIYE 
VEDOMOSTI. "I think that he does not take into account the 
consequences of his actions. I will not list all Ukrainian laws 
or articles of the Constitution that have been violated by this 
decision. I will provide just one typical example: The Crimean 
minister learned about his dismissal from the Crimean radio. It 
is very sad that Yuriy Meshkov is violating the same 
Constitution by which he swore and to which he pledged 
allegiance." 

</TEXT>

