<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Edict Introduces Privatization Certificates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Edict Introduces Privatization Certificates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304131594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0353 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev, 23 Apr -- An edict issued by the president of 
Ukraine entitles its citizens to a free share of the state 
property. According to this edict, in 1994 the citizens of 
Ukraine will be able to pay for the property to be privatized 
either from their privatization deposits in the banks or by 
privatization certificates. 
  Beginning 1 January 1995, property privatization 
certificates 
will remain the only tender in such payments. 
  The Ukraine Savings Bank is instructed to ensure that these 
certificates are issued to the citizens of Ukraine entitled to 
receive them in accordance with Ukraine legislation. 
  The property privatization certificates are valid until 31 
December 1996. 

</TEXT>

