<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Writes to Izetbegovic on Bosnia Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Writes to Izetbegovic on Bosnia Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404184994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin has sent a letter to 
Alija Izetbegovic, president of the presidency of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Yeltsin writes: 
  It is with great concern and disquiet that we have followed 
the developments surrounding Gorazde and Bosnia-Herzegovina as a 
whole. We strongly condemn any activity which results in the 
killing of the civilian population, Yeltsin writes in his letter 
to Izetbegovic. Russia has been taking all possible steps to end 
the bloodshed as soon as possible, to restrain the deadly 
currents of the war, and to restore a situation that would help 
in finding a political solution. To this end I sent the Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, to Belgrade. The activity of 
our special envoy Vitaliy Churkin in Sarajevo and in Pale was 
aimed at resolving the crisis. We insist on the Bosnian Serbs 
complying fully with the UN conditions regarding Gorazde, 
President Yeltsin says in his letter to Alija Izetbegovic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

