<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Date for Yeltsin Trip to Ukraine Undecided </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Date for Yeltsin Trip to Ukraine Undecided </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504104494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1017 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 25 Apr -- A visit to Ukraine by Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin, during which he is expected to sign a 
large-scale treaty between the two states, is being mooted, 
Yuriy Dubinin, special envoy of the Russian Foreign Ministry, 
said today at a news conference at the Russian Defense Ministry. 
  Yuriy Dubinin explained to the ITAR-TASS correspondent that 
agreement on this had been reached during Boris Yeltsin's 
meeting with Leonid Kravchuk in Moscow on 15 April. The exact 
date of the visit has not yet been finalized, the diplomat noted. 

</TEXT>

